To add php to your Windows path:
Right Click on My Computer and choose properties > Advanced Tab > Click "Environment Variables". {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/83/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/83/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/aid11676-v4-728px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":282,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"446","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Now add "C:\PHP;" to the very beginning. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5d/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/5d/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/aid11676-v4-728px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":245,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"387","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Now go to start > run > type: regedit and click OK.{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/1/13/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/13/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/aid11676-v4-433px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":248,"bigWidth":"433","bigHeight":"233","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\PHP\IniFilePath = C:\php to the registry. If you change your windows path instead of copying the dll files then you will need to restart your computer before php will work. Updating php is easier when you add it to your Windows path. So bookmark this page and go restart. Now is the best time since we are done with file placement. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/93/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/aid11676-v4-728px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":234,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"371","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

From the IIS Manager, click on the hostname of your server in the Connections panel on the left. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/29/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/29/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet5.jpg/aid11676-v4-728px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":252,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"399","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Double-click on the Handler Mappings icon. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9c/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/9c/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet6.jpg/aid11676-v4-728px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":252,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"399","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

From the Handler Mappings Actions panel, click on Add Module Mapping. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bc/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet7.jpg/v4-460px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/bc/Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet7.jpg/aid11676-v4-473px-Install-PHP-5-for-IIS-6-Step-11Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":396,"bigWidth":"473","bigHeight":"407","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
